The paper deals with the capacity of a communication channel that is characterized by inputs that are nonnegative and outputs that are corrupted by additive white Gaussian noise. This is a classic problem in information theory and communication engineering, which falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The specific channel being considered is a free-space optical intensity channel, which is a type of wireless optical communication channel. This suggests that the paper could also be classified under cs.COMM (Networking and Internet Architecture). The channel model involves the propagation of light through free space, which is a physical phenomenon that falls under the category of cs.PHYSICS (Physics and Society). The paper also mentions constraints on the input power due to battery and safety reasons, which suggests that it could be relevant to the field of cs.OH (Other Computer Science) or cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
